| BuildLang/buildc | Candidate exact-compute and proof-workbench layer for modular arithmetic, finite algebra search, and runtime receipts. | Runnable adapters against public SAIR-style tasks. |
| Model Foundry | Run local and hosted model baselines under contamination and receipt gates. | Pinned task/model/result packets. |

## Negative Controls

| Fixture | Rejection |
| --- | --- |
| `video_as_theorem_result_rejected` | A video/transcript can motivate a workflow but cannot establish a theorem result. |
| `empty_gather_body_as_source_body_rejected` | Empty static bodies are URL receipts only. |
| `competition_page_as_leaderboard_result_rejected` | Challenge descriptions do not prove result quality or leaderboard state. |
| `github_readme_as_mathematical_correctness_rejected` | Repo docs do not prove judge correctness or theorem correctness. |
| `source_lead_as_market_demand_rejected` | Infrastructure signal is not buyer validation. |
| `buildlang_replacement_claim_rejected` | BuildLang/buildc needs runnable contest adapters before replacement claims. |

